(opera music)

02:18.900 --> 02:22.438
(opera music)

02:50.400 --> 02:54.439
- Let me tell you the story of
a mild-mannered FBI instructor

02:54.470 --> 02:57.837
who was asked to create
a psychological profile
of a murderer -

02:57.870 --> 03:02.273
Garret Jacob Hobbs,
the Minnesota Shrike.

03:02.310 --> 03:04.744
He killed young women
that looked

03:04.780 --> 03:07.544
just like his daughter.
He killed them

03:07.580 --> 03:10.242
and he ate them.

03:10.290 --> 03:14.249
Will Graham understood
the way Hobbs thought.
That's how he caught him.

03:14.290 --> 03:17.953
He shot Hobbs dead while he cut
his daughter's throat.

03:17.990 --> 03:20.254
So, Will Graham was able
to save Abigail

03:20.300 --> 03:22.325
Hobbs' life. But

03:22.370 --> 03:24.361
the profile
that he created

03:24.400 --> 03:29.269
of her father was so vivid
that he couldn't escape it.

03:29.310 --> 03:31.460
- See.

03:31.510 --> 03:32.875
See.

03:32.910 --> 03:37.347
- And in an unconscious state...
he killed

03:37.380 --> 03:39.575
four more women.

03:42.520 --> 03:43.919
Cassie Boyle.

03:46.590 --> 03:48.581
Marissa Schuur.

03:48.620 --> 03:50.520
Georgia Madchen.

03:52.530 --> 03:53.827
Abigail Hobbs.

03:53.860 --> 03:56.829
He was able to save
Abigail Hobbs

03:56.870 --> 04:00.397
from her father, but he wasn't
able to save her from himself.

04:00.440 --> 04:02.260
He killed her

04:02.310 --> 04:04.266
and he ate her.

04:04.310 --> 04:07.802
At the very least,
he ate her ear. What happened

04:07.840 --> 04:11.048
to the rest of Abigail Hobbs
is locked away

04:11.080 --> 04:14.311
in the recesses of Will Graham's
traumatized mind,

04:14.350 --> 04:16.386
or so he would
have you believe.

04:16.420 --> 04:20.982
Something else you should know
about Will Graham: he has

04:21.020 --> 04:23.853
remarkable visual memory;

04:23.890 --> 04:27.826
he's keenly insightful
to the human condition; and...

04:27.860 --> 04:30.420
I would argue,
the smartest person

04:30.470 --> 04:32.335
in this room.

04:32.370 --> 04:34.338
He's capable

04:34.370 --> 04:36.861
of creating
a psychological profile

04:36.910 --> 04:40.277
of a completely different kind
of murderer.

04:43.080 --> 04:45.742
One that would
become his alibi.

04:57.960 --> 05:00.622
- Moment of truth.

05:00.660 --> 05:03.060
- If I only knew
what the truth was.

05:03.100 --> 05:05.660
- There's nothing wrong
with your instincts.

05:05.700 --> 05:08.066
- My instincts have not yet
arrived at conviction.

05:08.100 --> 05:12.332
- Mine have, with the benefit
of no previous involvement

05:12.380 --> 05:14.803
and no personal connections
to the accused.

05:14.840 --> 05:17.809
- Meaning I can't be impartial?
- Of course you can
be impartial,

05:17.850 --> 05:21.069
but right now you're not.
You have to believe something,

05:21.120 --> 05:25.409
as long as there is reason
and evidence to believe.

05:25.450 --> 05:27.850
You've got reason;
you've got evidence.

05:27.890 --> 05:30.859
Wi||_ Graham is
