22:28.480 --> 22:31.108
as an introverted personality.
He would like us to believe

22:31.150 --> 22:33.471
he places on the spectrum
somewhere

22:33.520 --> 22:35.408
near Asperger's
and autism.

22:35.450 --> 22:38.840
Yet he also claims
an empathy disorder.

22:38.890 --> 22:43.008
- You choose your words
very carefully, Dr. Chilton.

22:43.060 --> 22:45.028
You chose the word

22:45.060 --> 22:48.552
"claims."
- Will Graham has
never been diagnosed.

22:48.600 --> 22:50.693
He will not allow anyone
to test him.

22:50.730 --> 22:52.698
He has carefully
constructed

22:52.730 --> 22:55.528
a persona to hide
his real nature from the world.

22:55.570 --> 22:57.401
He wears it so well

22:57.440 --> 22:59.533
even Jack Crawford could
not see past it.

22:59.570 --> 23:01.777
- (Vega): But you did?

23:01.810 --> 23:04.938
- Mr. Graham and I had
no personal relationship

23:04.980 --> 23:09.076
for him to manipulate.
I have objectively examined him

23:09.120 --> 23:11.088
and the crimes
of which he is

23:11.120 --> 23:13.486
accused.
These murders

23:13.520 --> 23:16.956
were measured
and controlled.

23:16.990 --> 23:19.686
The confused man Will Graham
presents to the world

23:19.730 --> 23:22.551
could not _commit
those crimes,

23:22.600 --> 23:24.818
because that man is
a fiction.

23:26.900 --> 23:28.868
- So,

23:28.900 --> 23:31.630
you discount the encephalitis
he was suffering as a cause?

23:31.670 --> 23:35.208
- He managed his illness with
the help of his neurologist,

23:35.240 --> 23:37.447
whom he murdered
for his trouble.

23:40.110 --> 23:42.647
- Is Will Graham
an intelligent psychopath?

23:42.680 --> 23:44.989
- There is not yet a name

23:45.020 --> 23:46.942
for whatever Will Graham is.

23:46.990 --> 23:49.811
He kills methodically,

23:49.860 --> 23:53.921
and I believe would kill again,
given the opportunity.

23:56.630 --> 23:58.598
- Thank you,
Dr. Chilton.

23:58.630 --> 24:00.632
Your witness.

24:06.870 --> 24:08.599
- Dr. Chilton,

24:08.640 --> 24:11.700
Will Graham spent his time
catching murderers for the FBI.

24:11.750 --> 24:13.775
You don't see a contradiction
between that

24:13.820 --> 24:15.845
and your description
of a coldblooded killer?

24:15.880 --> 24:17.711
- No, I do not.

24:17.750 --> 24:21.618
Will Graham is driven by vanity
and his own whims.

24:21.660 --> 24:24.720
He has a very high opinion
of his intelligence.

24:24.760 --> 24:27.251
Ergo, he caught
the other killers

24:27.290 --> 24:29.121
simply to prove

24:29.160 --> 24:31.765
he was smarter
than all of them too.

24:34.040 --> 24:37.862
Saving lives is just as arousing
as ending them.

24:37.910 --> 24:39.901
He likes to play God.

24:54.260 --> 24:57.081
(keypad beeping)

24:57.120 --> 25:00.248
(door buzzer)

25:35.600 --> 25:37.864
- My admirer?
- Yes.

25:43.200 --> 25:46.704
The forensic report
from the crime scene.

25:46.740 --> 25:49.129
What do you see?

26:19.940 --> 26:23.649
(soft ambient pulse)

26:29.780 --> 26:32.783
(steady heartbeat)

26:47.170 --> 26:50.628
(door opening and closing)

26:57.080 --> 26:59.708
- I shoot Mr. Sykes once,

26:59.750 --> 27:01.377
collapsing lungs,

27:01.420 --> 27:05.208
tearing through his heart's
aorta and pulmonary arteries.

27:05.250 --> 27:07.684
(silenced gunshot)

27:11.090 --> 27:14.093
_ _ He will die _
believmg we were friends.

27:16.100 --> 27:17.863
It is his last thought.

27:23.770 --> 27:25.761
(Will panting)

27:30.440 --> 27:32.647
His death isn't personal.

27:44.730 --> 27:49.258
He is merely the ink
from which flows my poem.

28:03.880 --> 28:05.279
My tribute.

28:08.250 --> 28:09.979
This is my design.

28:11.990 --> 28:13.912
It's not the same killer.

28:16.420 --> 28:19.719
He murdered his victim first,
and then mutilated him.

28:23.030 --> 28:26.466
Cassie Boyle's lungs were
removed when _she was
still breathing.

28:26.500 --> 28:29.264
Georgia Madchen was burned
alive. What I...

28:29.300 --> 28:31.063
what... what I found

28:31.110 --> 28:34.409
of Abigail was cut off
while her heart was beating.

28:36.880 --> 28:40.839
- Then this...
is blunt reproduction?

28:40.880 --> 28:42.916
- You knew that already.

28:45.050 --> 28:47.018
- Would've liked
to have been wrong.

28:47.050 --> 28:49.280
- Occam's broom.

28:51.290 --> 28:54.350
You intentionally ignored facts
that refute your argument

28:54.400 --> 28:57.426
hoping nobody'd notice.
- You noticed.

28:57.460 --> 28:59.826
- Mm-hmm.

29:04.810 --> 29:07.131
- I wanted to dispel your doubts
once and for all.

29:09.580 --> 29:11.309
- My doubts about what?

29:11.350 --> 29:13.818
- Me.

29:17.990 --> 29:21.517
I want you to believe
in the best of me,

29:21.560 --> 29:24.051
just as I believe
in the best of you.

29:26.460 --> 29:28.928
This crime offered us both
reasonable doubt.

29:28.960 --> 29:31.167
- It offered us
a distraction.

29:33.170 --> 29:35.968
- Maybe this acolyte is giving
you your path to freedom.

29:36.000 --> 29:38.002
Even Jack is ready
to believe, Will.

29:47.250 --> 29:48.979
- It would be a lie.

29:56.390 --> 29:58.950
- I don't want you to be here.
- I don't want me to be here

29:58.990 --> 30:01.049
either.
- Then you have a choice.

30:01.100 --> 30:03.489
This killer wrote you
a poem.

30:07.970 --> 30:10.359
Are you going to let his love
go to waste?

30:21.220 --> 30:22.915
- I'm confused.

30:22.950 --> 30:26.408
You're going to abandon
your defense strategy,

30:26.450 --> 30:29.886
the entire case _
you've bUIlt, mid-trial.

30:29.920 --> 30:32.150
- Exciting,
isn't it?

30:32.190 --> 30:34.420
- And this seems reasonable
to you?

30:34.460 --> 30:36.894
- It's not only
reasonable;

30:36.930 --> 30:38.898
it's fashionable.

30:38.930 --> 30:41.091
There's a killer
on the loose,

30:41.140 --> 30:43.199
demonstrating all the hallmarks
of Will Graham's

30:43.240 --> 30:45.902
alleged murders.
- Do you think this killer

30:45.940 --> 30:48.909
committed the crimes
that you're accused of?
- Don't answer that,

30:48.940 --> 30:50.976
not_ in front of me.
It's inconsequential.

30:51.010 --> 30:54.116
- But is it true?
- You're being awfully
high and mighty, Dr. Bloom.

30:54.150 --> 30:56.118
Very ivory tower,
very reductive.

30:56.150 --> 31:00.314
Very far from the point,
which is the exoneration
of your friend

31:00.350 --> 31:02.386
Will Graham.
- And the point you're trying

31:02.420 --> 31:04.559
to make is reasonable doubt.
- That's a Win, yes.

31:04.590 --> 31:07.559
- The best you can
hope for is mistrial.
- That's also a win.

31:07.590 --> 31:10.195
- You won't be able to plead
unconsciousness again.

31:10.230 --> 31:12.460
- Your fast,
triumphant diagnosis

31:12.500 --> 31:14.559
of unconsciousness was
the best play we had.

31:14.600 --> 31:17.433
Now we have a better play.
Needless to say,

31:17.470 --> 31:20.109
I won't be calling you
to the witness stand.

31:20.140 --> 31:23.200
- Who's taking the stand
in my place?

31:44.200 --> 31:46.623
- I swear to tell the truth,
the whole truth,

31:46.670 --> 31:49.468
and nothing but the truth,
so help me God.

31:57.310 --> 31:59.699
- Good morning, Doctor.

31:59.750 --> 32:03.538
Please describe
your relationship
with Will Graham.

32:03.580 --> 32:06.344
- I was asked by Jack Crawford
to monitor Will's

32:06.390 --> 32:09.052
emotional well-being
while he worked on cases.

32:09.090 --> 32:11.354
I was never officially
his psychiatrist.

32:11.390 --> 32:13.426
- If you weren't his
psychiatrist, what were you?

32:13.460 --> 32:15.451
- I was meant
to be his stability.

32:17.460 --> 32:20.998
I failed him in that.
- How did you fail him?

32:24.040 --> 32:26.668
- I was unable to determine
if Will's condition was due

32:26.710 --> 32:30.271
to mental illness or stress
from his work at the FBI.

32:32.350 --> 32:35.342
My mistake was
never considering his innocence

32:35.380 --> 32:39.612
until the murder of a bailiff
from this courthouse.

32:39.650 --> 32:42.585
- And how did you know
about that, Dr. Lecter?

32:42.620 --> 32:46.056
- I have been asked to consult
on the case by Jack Crawford.

32:46.090 --> 32:49.059
He wanted a profile
of the bailiff's killer.

32:49.100 --> 32:51.193
- So, you believe

32:51.230 --> 32:53.596
the bailiff's murder was
committed by the same person

32:53.630 --> 32:56.360
guilty of Will Graham's
alleged crimes, yes?

32:56.400 --> 32:59.528
- Profiles aren't evidence;
they're opinion.
This is hearsay.

32:59.570 --> 33:02.073
- I will allow it.

33:02.110 --> 33:05.079
- Thank you,
Your Honor.

33:05.110 --> 33:08.568
- I believe there are alarming
similarities in the crimes, yes.

33:08.620 --> 33:10.576
- Will Graham accused you

33:10.620 --> 33:13.248
of the crimes for which
he now stands trial, and yet

33:13.290 --> 33:16.282
here you are, testifying

33:16.320 --> 33:19.027
on his behalf
for the defense.

33:19.060 --> 33:22.518
- Will rightfully couldn't
accept these actions to be his.

33:24.530 --> 33:28.159
A mind faced
with the possibility
of committing such deeds

33:28.200 --> 33:30.634
will find an alternative reality
to believe in.

33:30.670 --> 33:33.434
- You don't blame him
for that?

33:33.470 --> 33:35.438
- No.

33:35.480 --> 33:38.040
Will Graham is

33:38.080 --> 33:40.571
and will always be
my friend.

33:40.610 --> 33:43.170
- Your witness.

33:43.220 --> 33:47.111
- Dr. Lecter,
what was the cause

33:47.150 --> 33:49.459
of death
in the bailiff's murder?

33:49.490 --> 33:52.459
- A bullet to the heart.

33:52.490 --> 33:54.697
- Mm. And in Will Graham's

33:54.730 --> 33:57.119
victims, or alleged victims,
what was

33:57.160 --> 34:00.061
their cause of death?

34:00.100 --> 34:02.068
- Mutilation.

34:02.100 --> 34:04.807
- That's very different
from a bullet.

34:04.840 --> 34:08.435
- No two crimes of any killer
are going to be exactly
the same.

34:08.480 --> 34:13.144
The similarities--
- Your Honor, the witness's
personal beliefs and biases

34:13.180 --> 34:15.546
are driving his conclusions.
There are clearly

34:15.580 --> 34:17.673
two different killers
and two different cases.

34:17.720 --> 34:21.383
- Your Honor, there are
sufficient similarities
to con5ider this a defense.

34:23.660 --> 34:26.720
- I'm ruling this defense
inadmissible, Mr. Brauer.

34:26.760 --> 34:29.729
- Thank you, Your Honor.

34:29.760 --> 34:33.218
- (judge): All previous
testimony on the matter will
be stricken from the record.

34:38.470 --> 34:41.473
