36:14.400 --> 36:17.335
- (Jack): So, it appears that
the judge was murdered
in his chambers,

36:17.370 --> 36:20.737
and then he was hauled out here
to be put on display.

36:20.770 --> 36:24.649
- Not only is justice blind;
it's mindless and heartless.

36:24.680 --> 36:26.898
How did the killer get
so close?

36:26.950 --> 36:29.919
- No sign of a struggle.
Mutilation was post-mortem.

36:29.950 --> 36:32.544
- He was shot in the chest
just like the bailiff.

36:32.590 --> 36:35.559
Can't see the, uh, entry wound
because he removed the heart.

36:35.590 --> 36:39.378
- But there is an exit wound.
No slug - must have
taken it with him.

36:39.430 --> 36:41.591
- A trophy.

36:41.630 --> 36:43.291
- Doctor.

36:46.300 --> 36:49.360
With this judge's death,
there will be no verdict.

36:49.400 --> 36:51.630
No ending.
It'll start again,

36:51.670 --> 36:53.900
like the trial
never happened.

36:53.940 --> 36:56.374
But why?

36:56.410 --> 37:00.244
- Psychopathic violence is
predominantly goal-oriented,

37:00.280 --> 37:02.919
a means to a very
particular end.

37:02.950 --> 37:06.511
- So, the killer wanted
a mistrial?

37:06.550 --> 37:10.509
- It's an elegant,
if rather unorthodox, solution.

37:10.560 --> 37:13.654
- He spares Will a guilty
verdict and his life
for the moment.

37:13.690 --> 37:16.250
- Yes.
- The question is,

37:16.300 --> 37:18.495
is it the same killer?

37:18.530 --> 37:20.691
Is Will still on trial,
in your mind?

37:20.730 --> 37:22.698
- The use of a gun;

37:22.740 --> 37:25.368
death first,
mutilation last.

37:27.370 --> 37:30.999
I feel like St. Peter ready
to deny Will for the third time.

37:31.040 --> 37:33.645
I'm not sure this is
the same killer, Jack.

37:38.020 --> 37:40.409
- Excuse me.

37:45.860 --> 37:49.352
The killer exerted careful
control of the environment.

37:49.400 --> 37:52.494
He left very little
evidence behind.

37:52.530 --> 37:54.361
- Jeez, Jack.

37:54.400 --> 37:56.766
The trial was supposed
to put an end to this.

37:56.800 --> 37:59.303
Instead, the circus has
just added another ring.

37:59.340 --> 38:02.434
- And we're the clowns.
- Who's "we,"

38:02.480 --> 38:04.903
Jack?

38:04.950 --> 38:07.043
- I got off track.

38:07.080 --> 38:11.312
- You have to force yourself
out of this train of thought.

38:11.350 --> 38:13.318
The trial was going wrong

38:13.350 --> 38:15.955
before this murder.
The trial was going wrong

38:15.990 --> 38:18.720
because you wanted
to believe Will Graham.

38:18.760 --> 38:21.888
Who is he to you that makes you
want to risk everything for him?

38:21.930 --> 38:25.991
- A very cogent reminder
of the pitfalls of having faith
in one's fellow man, thank you.

38:26.030 --> 38:30.763
- Everyone at one point
or another has to_ leave
somebody behind.

38:30.800 --> 38:32.768
You've got
to cut him loose.

38:32.810 --> 38:34.778
Otherwise, the someone
being left behind,

38:34.810 --> 38:37.608
today or tomorrow...

38:37.640 --> 38:39.471
is gonna be you.

39:04.410 --> 39:06.537
(door buzzer)

39:06.570 --> 39:08.731
(door opening)

39:08.780 --> 39:10.771
(footsteps)

39:29.560 --> 39:31.767
(footsteps)

39:44.450 --> 39:46.645
(footsteps)

40:04.200 --> 40:06.020
- (Hannibal): Will.

40:16.580 --> 40:21.745
- I was hoping the verdict would
have helped focus your mind
to get better;

40:21.780 --> 40:26.114
make what happened to you
less terrifying and confusing.

40:28.860 --> 40:31.556
I can't exactly blame
your lawyer.

40:31.590 --> 40:34.081
- Faith in any sort
of legal justice has never been

40:34.130 --> 40:36.155
any more comforting
than a nightlight.

40:38.730 --> 40:41.699
- There are so many
miscarriages of justice

40:41.740 --> 40:45.699
when it comes to
identifying a psychopath.

40:45.740 --> 40:48.163
You could easily have been
misdiagnosed.

40:48.210 --> 40:52.044
- I've already been
misdiagnosed.

40:52.080 --> 40:54.514
- Not by the court.

40:54.550 --> 40:58.008
- No. Not yet.

41:03.560 --> 41:07.519
I walked out of that courtroom,
and I could hear my blood,

41:07.560 --> 41:09.118
like, uh...

41:11.130 --> 41:13.769
...a hollow drumming
of wings.

41:13.800 --> 41:16.894
And I had the...

41:16.940 --> 41:19.204
absurd feeling

41:19.240 --> 41:21.834
that whoever
this killer is...

41:24.580 --> 41:27.105
...he walked out
of that courtroom with me.

41:32.850 --> 41:35.648
He's gonna reach out to me.

41:37.660 --> 41:39.582
- What does he want?

41:45.870 --> 41:47.861
- He wants to know me.

41:55.210 --> 41:57.201
What do you want?

42:02.150 --> 42:04.141
- I want to save you.

